  "text": "The participants completed the Latifeh-Shafeq Marital Satisfaction Instrument [CITATION_1] . It is an empirically developed instrument containing 46 items under 10 dimensions. These dimensions are as follow: communication with nine items, commitment with five items, time together with four items, personality with five items, support with seven items, financial issues with t h r e e items, sexual relationship with three items, family of origin four, conflict resolution with two items and children issues with four items (See appendix A).",
